race.comment: OSTRAKA (8) was excellent first-up in the G3 Concorde Stakes, only collared late by Headwall, before finding the G2 Shorts a shade sharp second-up. Given a month between runs and tuned to the minute with a stylish trial win, he now looks ready to peak. GENEROSITY (15) impressed last start and had the better of OSTRAKA in the Shorts when storming home into third. Maps to settle off the speed again but the booking of McDonald is a huge push. Expect another explosive finish. ROTHFIRE (2) hasn't threatened in two runs back at the Valley but both in G1 company. Drawn sticky for Purton but with more room to move and if he can return to somewhere near his best, he will prove a handful. DISNECK (12) is flying, boasting a strong record at the track and trip and drawn to settle closer. A major player again. WITH YOUR BLESSING (7) brings G3-winning form and can give another bold on-pace sight.
